    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is MRI Pelvis Without Contrast effective for detecting cancer?",
        "answer": "Yes. Most pelvic cancers (cervical, endometrial, ovarian, prostate) produce visible masses or signal changes even without contrast. Additional contrast may be requested if finer vascular detail is needed.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does the scan take?",
        "answer": "Between 30 and 45 minutes, depending on whether high-resolution sequences are added.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Will I feel claustrophobic?",
        "answer": "The bore is open at both ends. Open-bore MRI machines and mild sedation are options at Cadabams Diagnostics for anxious patients.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat or drink beforehand?",
        "answer": "Absolutely. No fasting is required for an MRI Pelvis Without Contrast.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will my doctor receive the report?",
        "answer": "Scans are interpreted the same day; reports are dispatched electronically within 24 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What are the main mri pelvis no dye benefits?",
        "answer": "The key mri pelvis no dye benefits are a significant advantage for many patients. Primarily, it eliminates the risks associated with intravenous contrast dye, such as potential allergic-like reactions and the rare risk of nephrogenic systemic fibrosis in individuals with severe kidney disease. This makes it an excellent and safe imaging choice for patients with contrast allergies or impaired kidney function, while still offering highly detailed and diagnostically valuable images for many pelvic conditions."
      }
    ],
